Are ADATA SSD compatible with different operating systems? ADATA SSDs are designed in accordance with the Serial ATA International Organization standards and have undergone rigorous testing to ensure they work with various operating systems. If my computer only supports PCIe Gen3, can it still work with a PCIe Gen4 SSD? PCs that do not support PCIe Gen4 SSDs can still use the said SSDs. However, the SSDs performance will be limited to PCIe Gen3 Levels. Why is my SSDs capacity less than indicated on the packaging? Your PCs operating system and the SSD used different calculation methods. SSDs calculate capacity based on the decimal system, your PCs operating system uses the binary system. Capacity on packaging x 0.93 = SSD for approximate capacity. Why does my SSD's read/write not match the speed that was advertised? Is there something wrong with the product? Speeds may vary because different test software use different parameter settings and test methods, and the different testing environments and PC configurations may also have an influence. Besides, lack of free space will also affect writing speeds. Do I need to defragment my SSD? Since SSDs don't have mechanical drives, so there is no need for defragmentation. SSDs are designed to write data evenly on the entire drive as much as possible, thereby reducing excessive wear on any one location.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value for it's performance
reviews.reviewText: The ADATA 2TB SSD Legend 800 offers an impressive blend of performance and affordability. With its capacious 2TB storage, it accommodates vast data needs without compromising speed. The Legend 800's read and write speeds are commendable, enhancing overall system responsiveness and quick file transfers. Its reliability is noteworthy, backed by ADATA's reputation. The cost-efficient price tag places it squarely in the "good value for the money" category, appealing to budget-conscious users seeking ample storage and efficient operations. Whether for gaming, content creation, or everyday computing, this SSD provides a balanced solution that doesn't break the bank. You can't beat it's price point for size and reliability. Also I was lucky get this item on a lightning deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible value for the money
reviews.reviewText: I used this drive to upgrade the storage of my old gaming laptop that has a Gen3 M.2 interface. The out-of-box experience was great, seems to be working as advertised (in my case the speed is limited by the Gen3 interface) but I will soon use it in a new device that will take advantage of the Gen4 speeds. Temps are kept under control during everyday use and even while gaming.So far I have been completely satisfied with the product and the software tools ADATA provides are a great plus. I would highly recommend this product for anyone looking for decent performance on a budget.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works well but mind the possible overheating
reviews.reviewText: Being a Gen 4 M.2 NVME having super fast read and write speeds, your data transfers are a breeze. The side effects of this blazing fast transfers are that the stick will heat up rapidly.Make sure that you have a heat sink or a fan to keep it cool otherwise, it will cause some data corruption and cause the stick to malfunction.I tried to use it as a USB with a simple M.2 enclosure and that was not sufficient. It needed active cooling via a Fan.5 stars for what it does.
